# Documentation maintenance (required)

This project maintains technical docs in **`docs/`**. You MUST update them whenever this session adds or changes features, APIs, database schema, env vars, deployment, or architecture.

## When to update

Update docs if you change any of:

- Frontend routes, components, state, or API client
- Backend routes, auth, store, repositories, or schema
- Database tables, columns, or seed behavior
- Admin portal tabs or capabilities
- Environment variables or npm scripts
- Deployment or Docker setup

## What to update

| Change type | Update these files |
|-------------|-------------------|
| New/changed API endpoint | `docs/BACKEND-API.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md` |
| Frontend component or flow | `docs/FRONTEND.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md` |
| DB schema or tables | `docs/DATABASE.md`, `server/db/schema.sql`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md` |
| Admin features | `docs/ADMIN-PORTAL.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md` |
| Architecture / env / deploy | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` or `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md` |
| Any feature | `docs/CHANGELOG.md` (always append dated entry) |

## Changelog format

Append to `docs/CHANGELOG.md`:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD

### Short feature title
- Bullet summary of change
- Docs updated: BACKEND-API.md, DATABASE.md
```

## Index

Keep `docs/README.md` index accurate if new doc files are added.

## Do not

- Skip doc updates because the change seems small
- Put technical architecture only in README.md — use `docs/` for detail
- Delete or gitignore the `docs/` folder (docs are version-controlled)
